<br>
I have to say that managing my mana and agro was an important lesson for me to learn.  So important that I commonly watch the &quot;2 days to 50&quot; wizards get slaughtered on the march to the arena in Kael.  I've had one wizard accuse me of not casting.  I told him I know when to cast, and when not to cast.  I also know how to effectively use concussion.<br>
<br>
When they argue with me I just tell them, &quot;hey, you've been a wizard all of 48 hours, of course you know much better than a wizard who is played for 3 years.&quot; and leave it at that.<br>
<br>
Simply put, if KEI is not intended forplayers under 45, the spell should do a check of everyone in the group, not just the target.  That the spell does not do this, and that it's yet to be patched, tells me that Sony does not care to &quot;fix&quot; this oversight.  If you've ever been working on tradeskills in PoK and seen the same level 7 caster coming back every 5 minutes for KEI because he thinks he can hunt in LOIO with it, then you know what I'm talking about.<br>
<br>
Now players evidently feel that KEI is not a nice thing that happens now and then, they feel it's a necessity or even a right.  I've seen them get very exercised about it when no one is in PoK or Nexus casting it.  It's not an exploit, just poor design. <p><img src=http://24.26.194.142/sevepic.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nadiar>Nadiar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Mistyr Smartipants</span><br>  Posts: 1013<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/31/03 9:36:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25564.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nadiar.com/pics/sigico.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Define &quot;exploit&quot;</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If SOE intended KEI to be used on low levels, then why would they force you to group with them as the only way to cast on them? You can cast on them due to a bug. Working around a limitation (level limit) by use of this bug is an exploit, it's simple logic. As for the thread, it's in a forum called the Newbie Zone, so a good portion of posters are in fact newbies.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
